WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.102 --> 00:00:03.070
[Colter]
<i>Previously on</i> Tracker...

2
00:00:03.203 --> 00:00:04.171
-[Mel] You got a sec?
-What's up?

3
00:00:04.304 --> 00:00:05.673
I need you to look
into somebody.

4
00:00:05.807 --> 00:00:07.642
<i>It's for the Praiter</i>
<i>and Rockwell real estate case.</i>

5
00:00:08.141 --> 00:00:12.212
Hi. uh. Kurtis Lauper?
Reenie Greene. I'm looking
for witnesses to testify

6
00:00:12.346 --> 00:00:14.582
in a lawsuit against Praiter
and Rockwell Properties Group.

7
00:00:14.716 --> 00:00:17.484
I've been compiling evidence
for years.

8
00:00:19.186 --> 00:00:21.188
Everyone else broke.
But not me.

9
00:00:22.022 --> 00:00:23.691
[stammers] What happened
when you said no?

10
00:00:23.825 --> 00:00:25.894
They made me look insane.

11
00:00:26.026 --> 00:00:30.163
And when everyone
started believing them.
well. then I did feel nuts.

12
00:00:30.698 --> 00:00:33.601
You know you don't need
to fight this alone anymore.
right?

13
00:00:33.735 --> 00:00:35.870
I can't erase
what that company did.

14
00:00:37.437 --> 00:00:39.172
But I can make them
answer for it.

15
00:01:10.203 --> 00:01:13.106
[♪ "Leoncavallo: Pagliacci
Act 1: 'Vesti la giubba'"
playing on radio]

16
00:01:15.075 --> 00:01:16.310
[microwave beeps]

17
00:01:23.483 --> 00:01:25.520
[inhales deeply]

18
00:01:29.256 --> 00:01:30.725
[volume turns up]

19
00:01:33.795 --> 00:01:35.830
[microwave beeping]

20
00:02:02.890 --> 00:02:04.491
[♪ ominous music plays]

21
00:02:14.068 --> 00:02:15.670
[Maxine]
<i>You still can't reach him?</i>

22
00:02:15.803 --> 00:02:18.338
He should've been here
over two hours ago.
It's not like Kurtis.

23
00:02:18.472 --> 00:02:21.042
Well. there's a lot of pressure
right before trial. right?

24
00:02:21.174 --> 00:02:23.310
It's not the first time
I've seen a witness spook.

25
00:02:23.443 --> 00:02:26.446
He's only missed
one prep meeting.
That doesn't mean he's bailing.

26
00:02:26.581 --> 00:02:27.982
Maybe I should go check on him.

27
00:02:28.116 --> 00:02:29.316
Well. I'm right by his house.

28
00:02:29.449 --> 00:02:31.385
If it makes you feel better.
I'll swing by. okay?

29
00:02:31.519 --> 00:02:32.520
Yeah.

30
00:02:53.541 --> 00:02:54.776
Kurtis?

31
00:03:24.539 --> 00:03:25.873
[phone buzzing]

32
00:03:28.275 --> 00:03:30.912
-Hey. any luck?
-[Maxine] <i>Uh. I'm at his house.</i>

33
00:03:31.045 --> 00:03:33.346
I think you were right.
Something's wrong.

34
00:03:33.480 --> 00:03:34.949
Why? What'd you see?

35
00:03:35.083 --> 00:03:36.216
<i>Well. his truck's not here.</i>

36
00:03:36.349 --> 00:03:40.521
but his phone's in there
and his oxygen tank.

37
00:03:40.655 --> 00:03:43.524
<i>There's just no sign of him.</i>
<i>I mean. I could try to get in.</i>
<i>I guess. but--</i>

38
00:03:43.658 --> 00:03:45.560
No. no. no. no.
don't touch anything.

39
00:03:46.259 --> 00:03:48.529
<i>-You're right.</i>
<i>I'm gonna call the police.</i>
-Not yet.

40
00:03:49.229 --> 00:03:51.364
If he's missing.
I know who to call.

41
00:04:08.549 --> 00:04:11.284
He's been missing
seven hours at least.

42
00:04:11.418 --> 00:04:13.286
He was scheduled
to testify tomorrow.

43
00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:14.454
Yeah?

44
00:04:15.288 --> 00:04:17.491
What's this?
We got a phone over here.

45
00:04:19.827 --> 00:04:21.294
It's dead.

46
00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:22.864
You got Randy looking
for his truck?

47
00:04:22.997 --> 00:04:24.232
Yeah. couldn't find anything.

48
00:04:24.364 --> 00:04:25.700
No GPS.

49
00:04:25.833 --> 00:04:27.769
We called
all the local hospitals.
but no one's seen him.

50
00:04:27.902 --> 00:04:30.337
No. it can't wait.
We need to meet today.

51
00:04:31.404 --> 00:04:33.306
-Make it happen.
-[shutter clicks]

52
00:04:33.875 --> 00:04:35.743
Uh. Colter. this is Maxine.

53
00:04:35.877 --> 00:04:37.245
Maxine. how you doing?
Heard a lot about you.

54
00:04:37.377 --> 00:04:39.379
And I don't think I've heard
enough about you.

55
00:04:42.083 --> 00:04:44.252
Were you able to reach
the judge?

56
00:04:44.417 --> 00:04:45.586
Yeah. working on it.

57
00:04:45.720 --> 00:04:47.387
I woke up the poor clerk
who had a million questions.

58
00:04:47.522 --> 00:04:49.824
but I didn't wanna say too much
until we were face-to-face.

59
00:04:49.957 --> 00:04:52.860
-Smart.
-Okay. other than cold feet.

60
00:04:52.994 --> 00:04:54.829
what could have happened
to Kurtis?

61
00:04:54.962 --> 00:05:00.333
Well. worst case.
Praiter and Rockwell or someone
connected to the case took him.

62
00:05:00.467 --> 00:05:01.803
Is there evidence
backing that up?

63
00:05:01.936 --> 00:05:03.838
I mean. the case has been
really weird so far.

64
00:05:03.971 --> 00:05:07.440
Packages were delivered
to my office. Maxine's as well.

65
00:05:07.575 --> 00:05:10.077
Surveillance footage of us
at home.

66
00:05:10.812 --> 00:05:12.513
-At home?
-I know.

67
00:05:13.247 --> 00:05:15.950
Right after we made a new claim
to the suit.

68
00:05:16.617 --> 00:05:18.686
And Kurtis's testimony was key
to proving it.

69
00:05:18.820 --> 00:05:21.789
If we win. it could be fatal
to the company.

70
00:05:21.923 --> 00:05:23.691
You let the police know
about these threats?

71
00:05:23.825 --> 00:05:25.325
No. didn't rise to it.

72
00:05:25.458 --> 00:05:27.895
I mean. intimidation
is not uncommon
in lawsuits like this.

73
00:05:28.029 --> 00:05:29.864
Well. there's something here.

74
00:05:30.731 --> 00:05:32.133
I think it's blood.

75
00:05:32.834 --> 00:05:35.636
-Wait. what?
-Yeah. there was more.

76
00:05:36.504 --> 00:05:39.040
Think someone tried
to clean it up. Missed a spot.

77
00:05:40.675 --> 00:05:42.710
Reenie. there's a-a blade
missing from that knife block

78
00:05:42.844 --> 00:05:44.245
on the counter next to you.

79
00:05:46.314 --> 00:05:47.548
Here's what I'm thinking.

80
00:05:47.682 --> 00:05:51.085
I'm thinking our guy.
he. uh. came in here. right?

81
00:05:51.219 --> 00:05:52.954
Hid himself in this pantry.

82
00:05:53.087 --> 00:05:54.722
They ambushed Kurtis.

83
00:05:55.355 --> 00:05:57.191
And it was somebody who knew
what they were doing.

84
00:05:57.325 --> 00:05:58.559
There's no forced entry.

85
00:06:01.428 --> 00:06:02.429
This is on me.

86
00:06:03.164 --> 00:06:06.267
I brought Kurtis into this.
I pushed him
into doing the lawsuit.

87
00:06:06.399 --> 00:06:08.035
It's not your fault.
You're doing your job. Reenie.

88
00:06:08.169 --> 00:06:09.637
[phone buzzing]

89
00:06:10.338 --> 00:06:11.572
[Maxine sighs]

90
00:06:11.706 --> 00:06:13.875
-They went this way.
-Oh. I think that's the judge.

91
00:06:14.008 --> 00:06:15.743
Uh. you go ahead.
We're gonna take this.

92
00:06:15.877 --> 00:06:18.012
-Yeah.
-Hello.

93
00:06:18.145 --> 00:06:19.180
[door closes]

94
00:06:31.993 --> 00:06:33.761
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

95
00:06:51.913 --> 00:06:53.080
[grunts]

96
00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:01.923
[♪ theme music playing]

97
00:07:06.594 --> 00:07:08.262
-[Reenie] Yeah.
that's not Kurtis.
-[Colter] Mmm.

98
00:07:08.396 --> 00:07:10.932
It's the intruder.
Maybe one of them anyway.

99
00:07:11.065 --> 00:07:12.333
This guy was stabbed.

100
00:07:12.465 --> 00:07:13.834
Explains the blood inside.

101
00:07:13.968 --> 00:07:15.636
Yeah. What are you thinking?

102
00:07:15.770 --> 00:07:18.406
Kurtis. uh. he fights back.
stabs this guy.
kills him with a knife?

103
00:07:18.539 --> 00:07:22.143
I mean. he's an elderly man.
He uses intermittent oxygen.

104
00:07:22.276 --> 00:07:23.443
Adrenaline's a hell of a thing.

105
00:07:24.412 --> 00:07:27.281
-[sighs] What about
the missing truck?
-Not so sure.

106
00:07:28.716 --> 00:07:30.117
Someone was trying
to cover this up though. right?

107
00:07:30.251 --> 00:07:31.919
I'm thinking maybe
there's a third party.

108
00:07:32.820 --> 00:07:35.122
Maybe they... they took Kurtis
in his own truck?

109
00:07:35.256 --> 00:07:37.191
-Alive?
-I think so. yeah.

110
00:07:37.325 --> 00:07:40.094
And if they killed him.
we would have found
his body already.

111
00:07:40.227 --> 00:07:42.396
It's better just to make
the witness disappear. right?

112
00:07:42.530 --> 00:07:44.265
I mean. whoever did this
wanted to silence him.

113
00:07:44.832 --> 00:07:47.768
Well. they got sloppy.
If they made more mistakes.
I'll see 'em.

114
00:07:47.902 --> 00:07:51.072
Okay. Maxine's on her way
to the office. She'll handle
the legal side.

115
00:07:51.205 --> 00:07:52.340
I'll call the cops.

116
00:07:53.140 --> 00:07:54.575
Colter. you gotta find
this guy for me.

117
00:07:55.475 --> 00:07:57.345
Yeah. I'm on it.

118
00:08:00.147 --> 00:08:02.450
<i>Randy. you get any new hits</i>
<i>on Kurtis's truck?</i>

119
00:08:02.583 --> 00:08:07.555
Nada. I'm monitoring
traffic cams. toll roads.
No sightings. man.

120
00:08:07.688 --> 00:08:11.225
Listen. I saw a manual
for a mobile ham radio
at the house.

121
00:08:11.359 --> 00:08:12.560
I didn't see
the radio anywhere.

122
00:08:12.693 --> 00:08:14.795
I'm thinking maybe
he installed it in his truck.

123
00:08:14.929 --> 00:08:18.366
I'm sending you
a photo right now.
It has the ham's call sign.

124
00:08:18.498 --> 00:08:20.701
I like it. Let me see.

125
00:08:26.073 --> 00:08:28.009
Okay. I got the call sign.

126
00:08:28.142 --> 00:08:30.344
Maybe we get lucky
and it's still transmitting.

127
00:08:30.478 --> 00:08:31.979
[exclaims] There it is.

128
00:08:34.081 --> 00:08:35.583
-[computer beeps]
-Just sent you the location.

129
00:08:35.716 --> 00:08:36.751
<i>Got it.</i>

130
00:08:37.284 --> 00:08:39.020
<i>Hey. listen. Randy.</i> [grunts]

131
00:08:40.421 --> 00:08:43.491
Reenie mentioned something
about. uh. a threat coming in
at the office.

132
00:08:43.624 --> 00:08:47.395
Yeah. we had a courier come by.
dropped off a package.

133
00:08:47.528 --> 00:08:48.996
Could have something to do
with what happened here.

134
00:08:49.130 --> 00:08:50.598
-[door opens]
-Yeah. no doubt.

135
00:08:50.731 --> 00:08:52.566
I'm working to beef up
security. though.

136
00:08:53.134 --> 00:08:55.202
-Did you get an ID?
<i>-Uh. not yet.</i>

137
00:08:55.336 --> 00:08:58.105
Mel took a great photo.
just came out a little blurry.

138
00:08:58.239 --> 00:08:59.673
and so the facial ID
won't work.

139
00:08:59.807 --> 00:09:02.476
Okay. keep digging.
Keep an eye out. all right?

140
00:09:02.610 --> 00:09:04.812
-You got it. man.
-Hey.

141
00:09:04.945 --> 00:09:07.281
I got building security
to change the access codes.

142
00:09:07.415 --> 00:09:09.383
but nobody recognized
the courier from the photo.

143
00:09:09.518 --> 00:09:11.085
It's okay. Thank you for this.

144
00:09:11.218 --> 00:09:14.789
If I'd gotten
my phone out sooner
or taken a better picture...

145
00:09:14.922 --> 00:09:16.891
Come on.
This is not your fault.

146
00:09:17.024 --> 00:09:18.492
I'm just worried about Reenie.

147
00:09:19.326 --> 00:09:21.462
We really gotta find the guy
who did this.

148
00:09:22.196 --> 00:09:24.365
Mel... [chuckles]

149
00:09:25.633 --> 00:09:26.934
...you know I got you. right?

150
00:09:27.502 --> 00:09:31.238
-Yeah. I know.
-Okay. Let's get back to work.

151
00:09:43.350 --> 00:09:46.587
The circumstances are
beyond our control. Your Honor.
We need more time.

152
00:09:46.720 --> 00:09:49.690
So. your whole case hinges
on this witness's testimony?

153
00:09:49.824 --> 00:09:51.725
Oh. give me a break. Hoover.
You know damn well

154
00:09:51.859 --> 00:09:55.229
hundreds of people have signed
on to this lawsuit condemning
Praiter and Rockwell.

155
00:09:55.362 --> 00:09:57.064
You have seen
Kurtis's deposition.

156
00:09:57.198 --> 00:09:59.233
and you know his evidence
is undeniable.

157
00:09:59.366 --> 00:10:01.836
And I'm guessing their client
does as well. And here we are.

158
00:10:01.969 --> 00:10:04.905
And where is that. exactly?
You can't produce your witness.

159
00:10:05.039 --> 00:10:06.607
It's not exactly our problem.

160
00:10:06.740 --> 00:10:10.277
We can't produce Mr. Lauper
because your client
kidnapped him.

161
00:10:10.411 --> 00:10:11.546
[Hoover scoffs]

162
00:10:11.679 --> 00:10:12.947
Possibly worse.

163
00:10:13.080 --> 00:10:16.083
That's a pretty strong
accusation. Counsel.

164
00:10:16.217 --> 00:10:18.452
Do you have any evidence
to substantiate it?

165
00:10:18.587 --> 00:10:20.888
Uh. police report?
Missing person's complaint?

166
00:10:21.021 --> 00:10:22.990
We are actively investigating
the matter. Your Honor.

167
00:10:23.124 --> 00:10:24.191
Meaning they have nothing.

168
00:10:24.325 --> 00:10:26.660
He probably changed his mind
and ghosted you.

169
00:10:26.794 --> 00:10:29.997
Did you two rehearse
this little back-and-forth
pantomime thing?

170
00:10:30.131 --> 00:10:32.366
We remain ready to meet
the trial date. Your Honor.

171
00:10:32.500 --> 00:10:35.336
All we are asking for
is a little time.

172
00:10:38.205 --> 00:10:39.940
We'd like to be
kept in the loop.

173
00:10:40.074 --> 00:10:42.611
Well. we wouldn't wanna
keep you or your client
out of the loop. Devon.

174
00:10:42.743 --> 00:10:45.346
-I know they are so concerned.
-That's enough. Ms. Greene.

175
00:10:46.947 --> 00:10:48.449
You have 24 hours.

176
00:10:49.416 --> 00:10:50.684
Use them wisely.

177
00:10:50.818 --> 00:10:52.353
Thank you. Your Honor.

178
00:11:00.261 --> 00:11:04.064
You don't actually think
Praiter and Rockwell
kidnapped a witness?

179
00:11:05.099 --> 00:11:06.467
Actually. yes.

180
00:11:06.601 --> 00:11:09.470
[scoffs] Well. now
I'm looking forward to trial.

181
00:11:09.604 --> 00:11:12.239
We welcome
baseless allegations.

182
00:11:12.373 --> 00:11:14.041
Be sure to work those
into your cross.

183
00:11:14.175 --> 00:11:17.444
You should be looking forward
to my advice. Buckle up.

184
00:11:18.012 --> 00:11:21.550
-I hope you didn't
take this personally.
-Just business. right?

185
00:11:21.682 --> 00:11:24.985
I can assure you our client
had nothing to do with
your witness's disappearance.

186
00:11:25.119 --> 00:11:28.756
Oh. Well. does that extend
to sending us creepy
surveillance photos as well?

187
00:11:28.889 --> 00:11:30.625
-[phone buzzing]
-Oh. now we've threatened you

188
00:11:30.758 --> 00:11:31.992
in addition to your witness.

189
00:11:32.126 --> 00:11:34.161
How about we just table this
until trial. shall we?

190
00:11:34.695 --> 00:11:36.397
-Let's go.
-[Hoover sighs]

191
00:11:36.531 --> 00:11:37.566
Let's go.

192
00:11:39.601 --> 00:11:42.069
Hey. let's go ahead and
lock down the other witnesses.

193
00:11:42.203 --> 00:11:43.505
make sure they're protected.

194
00:11:43.638 --> 00:11:45.540
-Got it. You focus on Kurtis.
-Yeah.

195
00:11:45.674 --> 00:11:47.341
You know him better
than anyone.

196
00:11:47.474 --> 00:11:48.510
Yeah.

197
00:11:49.076 --> 00:11:51.445
-Thanks for having my back.
-Thank you.

198
00:11:53.380 --> 00:11:55.416
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

199
00:12:50.404 --> 00:12:51.438
[grunts]

200
00:13:10.725 --> 00:13:11.760
Okay.

201
00:13:14.361 --> 00:13:16.096
[phone buzzes]

202
00:13:17.064 --> 00:13:18.198
Please tell me it's good news.

203
00:13:18.767 --> 00:13:20.968
-Found the truck. It's totaled.
-Kurtis?

204
00:13:21.101 --> 00:13:23.871
<i>No sign that anyone was</i>
<i>in the truck when it crashed.</i>

205
00:13:24.004 --> 00:13:25.674
Wait. how is that
even possible?

206
00:13:25.806 --> 00:13:28.677
Gear shift is in neutral.
I think the car was ditched.

207
00:13:28.809 --> 00:13:30.177
They wanted us
to think they ran.

208
00:13:30.745 --> 00:13:32.547
Okay. so now what?

209
00:13:33.447 --> 00:13:36.250
Looks like you'd need
a car from here.
so either they stashed one.

210
00:13:36.383 --> 00:13:37.885
or maybe they stole one.

211
00:13:38.018 --> 00:13:40.354
All right. look.
you've got me and Randy.
Let me put you on speaker.

212
00:13:41.355 --> 00:13:42.956
Hey. what's up. man?

213
00:13:43.090 --> 00:13:44.925
Randy. any records
of a stolen vehicle
anywhere near my location?

214
00:13:45.059 --> 00:13:47.161
[Randy] Uh. let's find out.

215
00:13:48.362 --> 00:13:49.863
Nope. nothing reported today.

216
00:13:49.997 --> 00:13:53.500
All right. I passed a roadhouse
about a half a mile back.

217
00:13:53.635 --> 00:13:56.170
<i>The motel looked like</i>
<i>the last stop within miles.</i>

218
00:13:58.405 --> 00:14:01.342
Yeah. I see it. Looks like
the perfect place to get a car.

219
00:14:01.475 --> 00:14:03.077
<i>or to sit and wait in one.</i>

220
00:14:03.210 --> 00:14:05.079
That's what I'm thinking.
Can you check to see
if they have cameras?

221
00:14:07.749 --> 00:14:09.751
<i>If they do. they're air-gapped.</i>
<i>I'm not seeing anything.</i>

222
00:14:09.883 --> 00:14:11.318
All right.
I'm heading there now.

223
00:14:11.452 --> 00:14:13.187
Maybe someone saw something.
Thanks.

224
00:14:13.320 --> 00:14:14.355
[phone beeps]

225
00:14:58.700 --> 00:14:59.933
[Colter] Excuse me.

226
00:15:00.067 --> 00:15:02.269
Oh. Hey. man. Uh. nothing wrong
with day drinking.

227
00:15:02.403 --> 00:15:03.971
It's just we got this thing
called hours.

228
00:15:04.104 --> 00:15:06.808
[chuckles] No. I'm not. uh...
not here for the bar.

229
00:15:06.940 --> 00:15:09.176
I was wondering
if maybe you could help me
with something. I'm...

230
00:15:09.309 --> 00:15:12.747
I'm looking for this guy.
He's missing. Seen him?

231
00:15:14.181 --> 00:15:16.751
I wasn't working last night.
Nothing today.

232
00:15:17.317 --> 00:15:20.789
-Why are you looking for him?
-It's sorta what I do.
find people.

233
00:15:20.921 --> 00:15:23.525
[chuckles] Sounds mysterious.

234
00:15:23.658 --> 00:15:25.959
It can be. yeah. yeah.

235
00:15:26.093 --> 00:15:27.461
Your. uh...
Your security footage.

236
00:15:27.595 --> 00:15:29.597
is there a chance I could
get a look at that maybe?

237
00:15:29.731 --> 00:15:32.466
Yeah. I don't know.
I might have to
run that one by my manager.

238
00:15:32.600 --> 00:15:34.134
This the same person
that's having you carry

239
00:15:34.268 --> 00:15:35.570
all this heavy stuff
up this ramp?

240
00:15:36.704 --> 00:15:38.773
Okay. second thought.

241
00:15:39.607 --> 00:15:41.743
you help me. I help you?

242
00:15:44.612 --> 00:15:46.313
-Hand it over.
-Great.

243
00:15:50.819 --> 00:15:54.455
[chuckles] Wow.
you made that look really easy.

244
00:15:54.589 --> 00:15:56.390
-[Colter]
It's not my first time.
-[chuckles]

245
00:15:56.524 --> 00:15:57.659
All right. now.

246
00:15:59.293 --> 00:16:02.029
-Password.
-Right. I really
shouldn't be doing this.

247
00:16:02.162 --> 00:16:03.130
Probably not.

248
00:16:03.263 --> 00:16:04.298
[chuckles]

249
00:16:10.738 --> 00:16:14.007
[breathes deeply]

250
00:16:14.843 --> 00:16:16.310
[Colter] Okay. Keep going.

251
00:16:19.279 --> 00:16:20.314
Okay. that's him.

252
00:16:22.182 --> 00:16:26.220
Damn. what's the deal
with this guy anyway?
Is he in trouble?

253
00:16:27.087 --> 00:16:29.958
Something like that. yeah.
Pause it right there. will you?

254
00:16:30.457 --> 00:16:31.492
Thank you.

255
00:16:36.396 --> 00:16:38.533
-Grandpa just boosted that car.
-I know.

256
00:16:41.769 --> 00:16:44.506
One sec. Hold on.
That SUV. you recognize that?

257
00:16:44.639 --> 00:16:47.307
Nope. but it looks
shady as hell.

258
00:16:47.441 --> 00:16:48.977
-It does. doesn't it?
-Mm-hmm.

259
00:16:49.443 --> 00:16:51.478
Okay. I got what I needed.
Well. thank you very.
very much.

260
00:16:51.613 --> 00:16:53.848
-I appreciate you. All right.
-You're welcome.

261
00:16:54.381 --> 00:16:55.415
Hey.

262
00:16:56.116 --> 00:16:57.852
Come back anytime.

263
00:16:57.986 --> 00:16:59.721
I low-key wanna know
how this turns out.

264
00:17:00.755 --> 00:17:03.156
-Okay. Thanks again.
-Mm-hmm.

265
00:17:03.825 --> 00:17:05.125
[phone buzzes]

266
00:17:05.259 --> 00:17:06.561
Hey. you've got me and Randy.

267
00:17:08.161 --> 00:17:11.365
Kurtis is alone. on the run.
hot-wired a car.

268
00:17:11.498 --> 00:17:14.334
It didn't look to me
like it was the first time
he'd ever done that.

269
00:17:14.468 --> 00:17:17.337
<i>Sent you a picture of the car</i>
<i>he stole from a security cam</i>
<i>at the bar.</i>

270
00:17:17.471 --> 00:17:19.072
Who is this guy?

271
00:17:19.206 --> 00:17:21.743
I don't know. He kills
somebody in self-defense.
doesn't call the police.

272
00:17:21.876 --> 00:17:24.612
He covers it up.
ditches his car.
steals another.

273
00:17:25.847 --> 00:17:27.414
<i>Does he have</i>
<i>a criminal history?</i>

274
00:17:27.549 --> 00:17:29.349
Man. I did a background check
on this guy twice.

275
00:17:29.483 --> 00:17:31.920
Dude's a Boy Scout
from Vincennes. Indiana.

276
00:17:32.052 --> 00:17:35.188
High school education.
divorced. one stepdaughter.

277
00:17:35.322 --> 00:17:36.724
Something's not adding up.

278
00:17:36.858 --> 00:17:39.326
<i>There was a black SUV</i>
<i>that followed him out.</i>

279
00:17:39.459 --> 00:17:40.862
Maybe we're not
the only ones on his trail.

280
00:17:40.995 --> 00:17:42.564
Did you run the plates
on that stolen car?

281
00:17:44.264 --> 00:17:49.269
Okay. plates on
the stolen car pop up twice.
both times on the highway.

282
00:17:49.403 --> 00:17:51.438
<i>The first hit's a toll</i>
<i>on E-470.</i>

283
00:17:51.573 --> 00:17:55.777
The second was him merging
on to the I-70 Mountain Lane
Express this morning.

284
00:17:55.910 --> 00:17:57.645
and nothing since then.

285
00:17:57.779 --> 00:17:59.781
Maybe the person following him
ran him off the road?

286
00:18:00.347 --> 00:18:02.784
Or maybe he gave them the slip.
All right. thanks. you guys.

287
00:18:02.917 --> 00:18:05.787
Hey. Police identified the body
from Kurtis's house.

288
00:18:05.920 --> 00:18:07.722
He worked
for a trucking company.

289
00:18:07.855 --> 00:18:10.223
He's got a rap sheet
for assault and robbery.

290
00:18:10.357 --> 00:18:12.459
-Any connect with P&R?
-Not that I could find. no.

291
00:18:12.594 --> 00:18:14.227
What about Kurtis?
Any personal connection?

292
00:18:14.361 --> 00:18:15.897
Dude keeps
a pretty tight circle.

293
00:18:16.030 --> 00:18:19.466
Only people he talks to
are his stepdaughter. Jackie.

294
00:18:19.601 --> 00:18:21.134
and his ex-wife. Sienna.

295
00:18:21.268 --> 00:18:23.203
When's the last time
they were in contact?

296
00:18:23.337 --> 00:18:27.174
Uh. the stepdaughter.
a few weeks ago.
The ex-wife. yesterday morning.

297
00:18:27.307 --> 00:18:29.978
Maybe she knows something.
I'll pay her a visit.

298
00:18:35.349 --> 00:18:36.985
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

299
00:19:55.630 --> 00:19:57.131
[Kurtis]
Are you one of Lowell's men?

300
00:19:57.264 --> 00:19:58.365
[pistol hammer cocks]

301
00:19:58.498 --> 00:19:59.734
How did you find me?

302
00:20:01.234 --> 00:20:02.770
-[grunts]
-[screams]

303
00:20:02.904 --> 00:20:05.506
I said. how did you find me?

304
00:20:08.208 --> 00:20:09.811
[groaning. thuds]

305
00:20:10.778 --> 00:20:12.146
[coughing]

306
00:20:16.751 --> 00:20:18.052
[grunts]

307
00:20:18.886 --> 00:20:20.287
[coughing]

308
00:20:22.023 --> 00:20:23.057
[inhales deeply]

309
00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:36.637
[person] You hear me. Kurtis?
Lowell ain't gonna stop
until you're dead.

310
00:20:37.538 --> 00:20:41.075
[groaning]

311
00:20:41.209 --> 00:20:42.242
[grunts]

312
00:20:44.879 --> 00:20:46.214
[inhales deeply]

313
00:20:54.421 --> 00:20:55.957
[Kurtis grunts]

314
00:20:59.493 --> 00:21:00.628
[person groans]

315
00:21:06.299 --> 00:21:07.434
Kurtis Lauper...

316
00:21:10.037 --> 00:21:11.873
why don't you tell me
who you really are?

317
00:21:17.745 --> 00:21:19.013
Who sent you?

318
00:21:24.819 --> 00:21:28.756
Reenie Greene.
My name's Colter Shaw.
She hired me to come find you.

319
00:21:29.257 --> 00:21:30.290
[grunting]

320
00:21:32.026 --> 00:21:33.995
-I'll take a look at that.
-[grunts]

321
00:21:34.128 --> 00:21:35.163
-How's that feel?
-Ow!

322
00:21:35.295 --> 00:21:36.631
You got a high ankle sprain.

323
00:21:36.764 --> 00:21:40.467
Whatever's coming after you.
you're not gonna outrun it.

324
00:21:40.601 --> 00:21:42.103
That's for sure.

325
00:21:45.139 --> 00:21:46.406
[Kurtis] I like Reenie.

326
00:21:46.941 --> 00:21:48.441
She actually gives a crap.

327
00:21:49.944 --> 00:21:53.313
And I'm old enough to remember
that's a rare quality.

328
00:21:53.446 --> 00:21:55.216
but she shouldn't
have gotten involved.

329
00:21:55.783 --> 00:21:56.951
Hold this right there.

330
00:21:57.417 --> 00:21:59.386
What's this have to do
with your testimony?

331
00:21:59.921 --> 00:22:03.991
Everything I said
about that company
was the God's honest truth.

332
00:22:04.559 --> 00:22:07.728
but this isn't about that.

333
00:22:09.864 --> 00:22:11.464
[Colter]
Yeah. kinda gathered that.

334
00:22:15.803 --> 00:22:17.839
[police radio chatter]

335
00:22:25.880 --> 00:22:27.748
-Sienna Grimmer?
-Who are you?

336
00:22:27.882 --> 00:22:31.686
My name's Reenie Greene.
I'm an attorney. I'm looking
for your ex-husband.

337
00:22:31.819 --> 00:22:33.654
Wait. is Kurtis missing too?

338
00:22:34.454 --> 00:22:36.489
Uh. yes. no one's seen him
since yesterday.

339
00:22:36.624 --> 00:22:38.025
I know that you spoke with him
that morning.

340
00:22:38.159 --> 00:22:39.694
You know anything about this?

341
00:22:39.827 --> 00:22:40.928
No.

342
00:22:41.062 --> 00:22:43.965
I-I'm sorry.
Uh. who else is missing?

343
00:22:50.938 --> 00:22:52.607
[Colter] Your visitor here
is from Louisiana.

344
00:22:53.341 --> 00:22:54.275
Long way.

345
00:22:54.407 --> 00:22:55.442
[phone buzzing]

346
00:22:57.345 --> 00:23:00.848
-Reenie. I got Kurtis.
-Oh. great. Kurtis. hey.

347
00:23:00.982 --> 00:23:02.984
I shouldn't be talking to you.
It's not safe.

348
00:23:03.117 --> 00:23:04.986
-Are you with Jackie?
-[Colter] <i>Who's Jackie?</i>

349
00:23:05.119 --> 00:23:06.153
Stepdaughter.

350
00:23:06.754 --> 00:23:09.023
-No. Why?
-She's missing.

351
00:23:09.156 --> 00:23:11.259
<i>I'm at your ex-wife's house</i>
<i>with the police.</i>

352
00:23:11.391 --> 00:23:12.693
<i>Look. she didn't turn up</i>
<i>for work today.</i>

353
00:23:12.827 --> 00:23:14.829
Sienna went to her place.
but she's gone.

354
00:23:14.962 --> 00:23:16.163
I'm gonna kill them all.

355
00:23:16.731 --> 00:23:17.765
Who did this?

356
00:23:18.699 --> 00:23:19.934
Lowell Parker.

357
00:23:21.068 --> 00:23:22.370
Dixie Mafia.

358
00:23:22.503 --> 00:23:25.273
Runs guns. drugs.
anything he can
get his hands on.

359
00:23:25.405 --> 00:23:26.439
You work for him?

360
00:23:27.208 --> 00:23:29.810
Muscle. Long time ago.

361
00:23:31.411 --> 00:23:34.081
But I disappeared.
took the name
of a boyhood friend

362
00:23:34.215 --> 00:23:36.684
who'd died on a fishing trip.

363
00:23:37.484 --> 00:23:39.452
<i>Moved a few states over.</i>

364
00:23:40.221 --> 00:23:41.722
<i>Thought it was all behind me.</i>

365
00:23:41.856 --> 00:23:44.091
But why would he take
your stepdaughter
after so many years?

366
00:23:44.225 --> 00:23:46.560
'Cause he found me.
and now he wants
blood for blood.

367
00:23:46.694 --> 00:23:49.563
-You agreeing to testify
blew your cover.
-Has to be it.

368
00:23:49.697 --> 00:23:51.966
I never should have gotten
involved in that lawsuit.

369
00:23:53.935 --> 00:23:56.604
-I have to find Jackie.
-I can help you.

370
00:23:56.737 --> 00:24:00.141
All right. grab your stuff.
Let's go. Thanks. Reenie.

371
00:24:02.043 --> 00:24:04.477
Okay. come on. Easy.
What did Parker want?

372
00:24:05.413 --> 00:24:07.581
-Revenge.
-Revenge for what?

373
00:24:07.715 --> 00:24:09.482
[panting] I made a mistake.

374
00:24:10.584 --> 00:24:11.919
Parker trusted me.

375
00:24:12.954 --> 00:24:15.990
Had me looking after
his daughter. Only child.

376
00:24:17.725 --> 00:24:19.961
-She was a handful.
-Easy here.

377
00:24:20.094 --> 00:24:21.629
In and out of trouble.

378
00:24:22.430 --> 00:24:24.932
I mean. she was a sweet kid.
but... [breathing heavily]

379
00:24:26.634 --> 00:24:28.302
...she had a few stints
in rehab.

380
00:24:29.170 --> 00:24:31.172
It was my job to keep her safe.

381
00:24:32.974 --> 00:24:34.642
But she was hooked on blues.

382
00:24:35.409 --> 00:24:37.511
And one day.
I went to pick her up.

383
00:24:38.579 --> 00:24:40.480
And she was dead
in the bathtub.

384
00:24:41.916 --> 00:24:43.284
OD'd.

385
00:24:43.417 --> 00:24:44.652
Blame you for that?

386
00:24:44.785 --> 00:24:46.988
Easier to blame me than her.
I guess.

387
00:24:48.556 --> 00:24:52.126
Now Jackie's in danger
because of me.

388
00:24:55.262 --> 00:24:56.297
We'll find her.

389
00:24:59.533 --> 00:25:01.469
Kurtis isn't
who we thought he was.

390
00:25:01.602 --> 00:25:04.672
He was a bodyguard
for Lowell Parker.
a Dixie Mafia boss.

391
00:25:04.805 --> 00:25:06.807
So this has nothing to do
with Praiter and Rockwell?

392
00:25:06.941 --> 00:25:09.210
No. I mean. they're not
the ones that came after him.

393
00:25:10.077 --> 00:25:12.680
And we made an accusation
in front of the judge
that we can't support.

394
00:25:12.813 --> 00:25:15.016
Well. not necessarily.

395
00:25:16.183 --> 00:25:17.651
Parker was tipped somehow.

396
00:25:17.785 --> 00:25:20.955
and Kurtis seems to think
that the lawsuit
blew his cover.

397
00:25:21.822 --> 00:25:23.657
But his name
was never public record.

398
00:25:23.791 --> 00:25:27.595
so even if Praiter and Rockwell
didn't commit the actual crime.

399
00:25:27.728 --> 00:25:29.497
someone must have tapped
the first domino.

400
00:25:30.031 --> 00:25:31.832
-There's a mole.
-Yeah.

401
00:25:32.700 --> 00:25:35.002
But we have to put
the whole thing
on the back burner for now.

402
00:25:35.136 --> 00:25:36.537
[Maxine exhales forcefully]

403
00:25:36.670 --> 00:25:38.372
Okay. just until we know that
Kurtis's stepdaughter's safe.

404
00:25:38.507 --> 00:25:41.876
Okay. Well. let me do
some digging on my end.

405
00:25:42.009 --> 00:25:42.943
[phone buzzing]

406
00:25:43.077 --> 00:25:44.513
-Keep me posted.
-Will do.

407
00:25:45.413 --> 00:25:46.447
[sighs]

408
00:25:49.016 --> 00:25:51.719
-Hello.
-[caller] <i>Reenie Greene?</i>

409
00:25:52.720 --> 00:25:54.088
Who's this?

410
00:25:55.656 --> 00:25:56.824
Lowell Parker.

411
00:25:57.725 --> 00:25:58.793
How'd you get this number?

412
00:25:58.926 --> 00:26:01.429
<i>Oh. does that really matter?</i>

413
00:26:02.396 --> 00:26:03.631
No. it does not.

414
00:26:04.698 --> 00:26:08.436
What matters is I need this
to happen without the cops.

415
00:26:09.003 --> 00:26:10.838
You need what
to happen exactly?

416
00:26:10.971 --> 00:26:14.108
I was really hoping you weren't
gonna waste my time.

417
00:26:14.875 --> 00:26:16.143
[bound person whimpering]

418
00:26:16.277 --> 00:26:18.312
But just so you understand...

419
00:26:18.446 --> 00:26:21.749
[gasps] Help me. Help me.
Please. help me.
Please. please help me.

420
00:26:21.882 --> 00:26:23.217
-[sobbing]
-Jackie. is that you?

421
00:26:23.350 --> 00:26:25.252
You seem like a smart gal.

422
00:26:26.253 --> 00:26:30.324
You do exactly what I say.
and Jackie walks.

423
00:26:37.398 --> 00:26:39.433
[♪ tense music playing]

424
00:26:44.238 --> 00:26:46.774
-[Reenie] Hey.
-Hey. you sure
you weren't followed?

425
00:26:46.907 --> 00:26:48.242
Yes. I stuck to the plan.

426
00:26:48.375 --> 00:26:51.278
Now. this is the location
of the meet.

427
00:26:51.412 --> 00:26:54.381
Parker said that he wants me
to deliver Kurtis personally.

428
00:26:54.949 --> 00:26:56.585
Then Jackie walks.

429
00:26:57.384 --> 00:26:58.752
I don't trust it.

430
00:26:58.886 --> 00:27:01.622
I know. but the best way
to minimize risk
and protect Jackie

431
00:27:02.490 --> 00:27:04.526
is to follow
the ransom demands exactly.

432
00:27:05.759 --> 00:27:07.428
I don't wanna mess around
with this.

433
00:27:07.562 --> 00:27:08.996
It's my life for hers.

434
00:27:09.864 --> 00:27:12.500
And I'm okay with that.
I'm on borrowed time anyway.

435
00:27:13.535 --> 00:27:15.803
If the last thing I do
is save Jackie. then...

436
00:27:16.605 --> 00:27:17.972
then at least I've done
something good.

437
00:27:18.472 --> 00:27:20.609
I'm not just sending you
in there to get killed.

438
00:27:20.741 --> 00:27:23.777
Hey. I'm not gonna let
that happen to anybody.

439
00:27:34.722 --> 00:27:36.824
[breathes shakily] Okay.
Reenie's almost at the meet.

440
00:27:36.957 --> 00:27:39.827
Yeah. I know.
I'm watching it too.
but come here. Check this out.

441
00:27:42.997 --> 00:27:45.466
[Mel] Oh. my God. that's...
that's him. That's the courier.

442
00:27:45.600 --> 00:27:47.368
Turns out his uniform is fake.

443
00:27:47.501 --> 00:27:50.871
I traced it back
to the manufacturer.
followed the local sales.

444
00:27:51.005 --> 00:27:54.308
Nice. Any connection
to Praiter and Rockwell?

445
00:27:54.942 --> 00:27:58.212
I just got the ID.
but at first glance.
I don't see anything.

446
00:27:58.746 --> 00:28:00.314
Same with the Dixie Mafia.

447
00:28:00.447 --> 00:28:03.717
No. no. No. he's gotta
fit in this somehow.

448
00:28:03.851 --> 00:28:05.953
Can I see
his employment history?

449
00:28:06.453 --> 00:28:07.988
Certainly.

450
00:28:14.361 --> 00:28:15.896
-You see something?
-[gasps]

451
00:28:17.599 --> 00:28:18.633
[Mel] Maybe. I...

452
00:28:19.700 --> 00:28:21.769
I think I gotta call Maxine.

453
00:28:23.070 --> 00:28:24.104
Okay.

454
00:28:25.406 --> 00:28:26.440
[sighs]

455
00:28:29.043 --> 00:28:30.344
[Reenie] We're almost there.

456
00:28:32.780 --> 00:28:34.348
Why are you doing this for me?

457
00:28:36.685 --> 00:28:38.219
I'm not a good man.

458
00:28:40.321 --> 00:28:41.889
Come on.

459
00:28:42.022 --> 00:28:45.326
You took a risk to help
thousands of people
in this lawsuit.

460
00:28:46.193 --> 00:28:47.895
You're a better man
than you think.

461
00:28:48.495 --> 00:28:50.197
I was Parker's enforcer.

462
00:28:51.432 --> 00:28:53.267
The things I did...

463
00:28:54.268 --> 00:28:56.538
I didn't deserve
the second chance I got.

464
00:29:00.007 --> 00:29:01.041
You know.

465
00:29:02.577 --> 00:29:07.214
the first time I ever
stepped into a courtroom.
I was actually the defendant.

466
00:29:09.216 --> 00:29:11.752
Yeah. I know.
I was 14 years old.

467
00:29:12.621 --> 00:29:17.057
Broke into a local
department store and stole
a beautiful Chanel clutch.

468
00:29:17.992 --> 00:29:20.761
-It was worth
thousands of dollars.
-Why?

469
00:29:21.529 --> 00:29:22.564
I don't know.

470
00:29:23.632 --> 00:29:24.965
My sister dared me.

471
00:29:26.467 --> 00:29:29.203
It was just me and her
at the time.
We were on our own.

472
00:29:29.336 --> 00:29:30.971
You know.
my dad was deployed out.

473
00:29:31.105 --> 00:29:33.774
My mom.
she was basically absent.

474
00:29:35.242 --> 00:29:38.713
[sighs] It was just something
that we would never be able
to afford.

475
00:29:39.980 --> 00:29:42.850
She said no one would notice.
No one would care.

476
00:29:44.118 --> 00:29:46.487
I just wanted to see
if she was right.

477
00:29:48.222 --> 00:29:52.860
Anyway. point is.
is that they assigned me
this public defender.

478
00:29:53.494 --> 00:29:54.663
I'll never forget her.

479
00:29:55.764 --> 00:29:57.498
She said that life
goes two ways.

480
00:29:58.499 --> 00:30:01.402
"You're either the painter
or you're the paint."

481
00:30:03.638 --> 00:30:05.272
I made my choice.

482
00:30:07.308 --> 00:30:08.809
So did you.

483
00:30:10.444 --> 00:30:12.714
We choose who we are. you know.

484
00:30:17.585 --> 00:30:19.119
My real name is Eugene.

485
00:30:20.487 --> 00:30:24.191
Guys used to call me
Gene Gene the Dancing Machine.

486
00:30:27.762 --> 00:30:28.862
<i>Gong Show?</i>

487
00:30:29.830 --> 00:30:31.198
It's before your time.

488
00:30:33.568 --> 00:30:34.602
You liked to dance?

489
00:30:35.302 --> 00:30:36.604
No. the opposite.

490
00:30:40.341 --> 00:30:41.375
Okay.

491
00:30:42.510 --> 00:30:44.512
I may just stick with
Kurtis though.

492
00:30:46.748 --> 00:30:47.948
[Reenie chuckles]

493
00:30:52.152 --> 00:30:54.188
All right.

494
00:30:56.725 --> 00:30:58.992
-You ready?
-Here we go.

495
00:31:17.077 --> 00:31:19.514
[henchman. on radio]
<i>Car just pulled up.</i>
<i>Two occupants.</i>

496
00:31:22.116 --> 00:31:23.217
[choking]

497
00:31:24.552 --> 00:31:26.688
-...go. huh?
-This is about Jackie.

498
00:31:26.821 --> 00:31:28.055
No matter what happens to me.

499
00:31:28.188 --> 00:31:30.391
all I care about
is that she gets out of this.

500
00:31:30.525 --> 00:31:31.526
And watch your back.

501
00:31:31.659 --> 00:31:33.227
-Kurtis.
-[henchman] Let's go.

502
00:31:45.774 --> 00:31:46.875
Hands on the wheel.

503
00:31:48.375 --> 00:31:49.577
-[kick lands]
-[grunts]

504
00:31:52.246 --> 00:31:53.548
[pants]

505
00:31:56.651 --> 00:31:58.252
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

506
00:32:05.527 --> 00:32:06.795
[henchman groans]

507
00:32:10.397 --> 00:32:12.499
[shells clatter]

508
00:32:17.271 --> 00:32:19.239
[Jackie whimpering]

509
00:32:23.878 --> 00:32:26.313
-[breathing heavily] Jackie.
-[sobbing]

510
00:32:29.216 --> 00:32:30.919
You look like hell. Gene.

511
00:32:31.452 --> 00:32:32.687
Let her go.

512
00:32:33.721 --> 00:32:34.923
This is between us.

513
00:32:35.055 --> 00:32:36.290
I'm here.

514
00:32:37.057 --> 00:32:38.158
Do whatever you want with me.

515
00:32:38.292 --> 00:32:41.261
[groans]
I can't let you off that easy.

516
00:32:42.095 --> 00:32:43.397
We had a deal.

517
00:32:44.298 --> 00:32:45.767
My life for hers.

518
00:32:47.669 --> 00:32:49.002
[muffled screaming]

519
00:32:51.773 --> 00:32:53.073
I didn't have that choice.

520
00:32:54.475 --> 00:32:57.912
I gave you
the most important job.
and you screwed it up.

521
00:32:59.514 --> 00:33:00.849
My daughter's dead...

522
00:33:05.285 --> 00:33:06.621
because you dropped the ball.

523
00:33:09.924 --> 00:33:13.026
Now you're gonna get to see
what I do to somebody you love.

524
00:33:13.828 --> 00:33:15.730
I-I'm begging you. Lowell.
please.

525
00:33:22.804 --> 00:33:24.004
[henchman 1 grunts]

526
00:33:24.137 --> 00:33:26.006
[both grunting]

527
00:33:29.343 --> 00:33:30.310
[henchman 1 gurgling]

528
00:33:30.444 --> 00:33:31.513
[Colter grunts]

529
00:33:32.145 --> 00:33:33.180
[henchman 2 groaning]

530
00:33:34.649 --> 00:33:35.683
[crying]

531
00:33:37.050 --> 00:33:39.119
-[shrieks]
-[Kurtis] No!

532
00:33:40.420 --> 00:33:42.322
-[blow lands]
-[Kurtis grunting. wheezing]

533
00:33:48.362 --> 00:33:50.832
[Kurtis breathing heavily]

534
00:33:52.901 --> 00:33:54.903
-[grunts]
-No. no. no. No!

535
00:33:59.974 --> 00:34:01.408
[groaning]

536
00:34:01.910 --> 00:34:04.111
You still got a lot of fight
in you. huh. old man?

537
00:34:04.244 --> 00:34:06.113
[both grunting. groaning]

538
00:34:22.730 --> 00:34:23.965
[grunts]

539
00:34:25.533 --> 00:34:27.569
[wheezing]

540
00:34:30.270 --> 00:34:33.942
Maybe we need to
help nature along a little bit.

541
00:34:39.179 --> 00:34:42.850
But I want you to see something
before your number's up.

542
00:35:01.970 --> 00:35:03.170
[all screaming]

543
00:35:04.939 --> 00:35:06.373
-Where is he?
-Behind!

544
00:35:06.507 --> 00:35:07.942
[henchmen shouting]

545
00:35:09.944 --> 00:35:11.079
[gunfire continues]

546
00:35:11.713 --> 00:35:13.246
[tires squeal]

547
00:35:14.616 --> 00:35:16.618
-[both grunt]
-[tires screech]

548
00:35:16.751 --> 00:35:17.952
[henchman 1] Behind the car!

549
00:35:21.589 --> 00:35:23.190
-[henchman 2 grunts]
-[tires screech]

550
00:35:27.729 --> 00:35:28.663
Hey!

551
00:35:29.731 --> 00:35:30.965
[grunts. groans]

552
00:35:31.099 --> 00:35:32.033
Come here. You all right?

553
00:35:32.165 --> 00:35:33.701
-[Jackie gasps] Thank you.
-Yeah.

554
00:35:35.536 --> 00:35:38.138
-[Kurtis] Jackie? Jackie.
-[Jackie panting] Hi.
I'm here. I'm okay.

555
00:35:39.073 --> 00:35:41.843
-I'm okay.
-Easy. now. Take it easy.

556
00:35:41.976 --> 00:35:44.378
-Is he gonna be okay?
-Just needs an ambulance.

557
00:35:45.079 --> 00:35:46.413
Stay with us. Kurtis.

558
00:35:46.547 --> 00:35:47.915
[phone dialing 911]

559
00:35:48.950 --> 00:35:50.585
[line ringing]

560
00:35:57.190 --> 00:35:58.993
Thanks. Kurtis.
We'll see you soon.

561
00:36:01.461 --> 00:36:03.363
-Hey. that was Kurtis.
-Hey.

562
00:36:03.497 --> 00:36:07.167
He is relentless.
He wants to testify as soon
as the hospital discharges him.

563
00:36:07.300 --> 00:36:09.537
Ooh. a man after my own heart.

564
00:36:10.571 --> 00:36:12.305
And here comes the fun part.

565
00:36:13.808 --> 00:36:15.275
I thought we'd pushed
to next week.

566
00:36:15.409 --> 00:36:17.111
-What's up?
-Oh. Everything.

567
00:36:18.178 --> 00:36:20.548
[chuckles] We can save
the high school games
for the courtroom.

568
00:36:20.682 --> 00:36:23.417
-Oh. you're not gonna
be a part of that.
-Mmm. Shame.

569
00:36:24.284 --> 00:36:25.887
[Devon] Unless you have
something important to share.

570
00:36:26.020 --> 00:36:27.155
I'm late to meet my wife.

571
00:36:27.287 --> 00:36:29.924
Actually. uh. Devon.
quick question for you.

572
00:36:30.058 --> 00:36:33.260
You were a summer associate
at Danvers and Saperstein.
correct?

573
00:36:35.730 --> 00:36:38.166
-I was.
-Out of their New Orleans
office. yes?

574
00:36:38.298 --> 00:36:39.834
Yeah.

575
00:36:39.967 --> 00:36:43.705
And that's the same firm
who represents Lowell Parker
on RICO charges?

576
00:36:43.838 --> 00:36:46.206
-What's this about?
-We're hoping you can tell us.

577
00:36:49.376 --> 00:36:50.745
Nothing?

578
00:36:50.878 --> 00:36:52.947
Because that firm
employed the courier

579
00:36:53.081 --> 00:36:56.084
who delivered some
pretty interesting photographs
of us to our offices.

580
00:36:56.651 --> 00:36:59.787
Take your time. Devon.
I keep forgetting you failed
the bar. what was it?

581
00:36:59.921 --> 00:37:01.723
-Five times?
-Oh. five times.

582
00:37:01.856 --> 00:37:04.192
[chuckles] I just don't know
what you're talking about.

583
00:37:04.324 --> 00:37:05.693
[Reenie] Oh. but I bet you do.

584
00:37:06.426 --> 00:37:08.596
If you need it spelled out
for you. I can help you out.

585
00:37:08.730 --> 00:37:12.033
It was you who gave up Kurtis.
Ring a bell now?

586
00:37:12.166 --> 00:37:14.401
You recognized him.
served him up to Parker.

587
00:37:14.535 --> 00:37:16.303
For what? Money. an old favor?

588
00:37:16.436 --> 00:37:19.173
I don't know exactly.
but I'm pretty sure this is
the end of your career.

589
00:37:19.707 --> 00:37:21.909
-You're speculating.
-Oh. I don't speculate.

590
00:37:22.043 --> 00:37:23.211
[Devon scoffs]

591
00:37:26.881 --> 00:37:28.716
-What do you want?
-Justice

592
00:37:29.349 --> 00:37:31.652
for every single person
that Praiter and Rockwell
wronged.

593
00:37:31.786 --> 00:37:33.386
Starting with
a favorable settlement

594
00:37:33.521 --> 00:37:36.157
in our inboxes
no later than tomorrow morning.

595
00:37:36.289 --> 00:37:37.992
Why would I do that?

596
00:37:38.126 --> 00:37:41.261
Because we can drop
this whole thing to
the bar association right now.

597
00:37:41.996 --> 00:37:45.432
or we can give you a few weeks.
you know.

598
00:37:45.566 --> 00:37:46.901
let you get
your ducks in a row.

599
00:37:47.034 --> 00:37:49.269
-That would be very nice of us.
-Mm-hmm.

600
00:37:51.338 --> 00:37:52.740
Best and only deal.

601
00:37:53.440 --> 00:37:54.474
[scoffs]

602
00:37:55.475 --> 00:37:56.443
[sighs]

603
00:37:56.577 --> 00:37:58.278
I'll start drafting it now.

604
00:37:59.781 --> 00:38:00.815
[Reenie] Hmm.

605
00:38:00.948 --> 00:38:02.349
[Maxine chuckles]

606
00:38:03.283 --> 00:38:06.187
[Reenie] It's just harder
than it looks.

607
00:38:06.319 --> 00:38:08.990
[gunfire]

608
00:38:09.123 --> 00:38:10.091
[tin can clatters]

609
00:38:10.224 --> 00:38:12.927
-Something like that. okay?
-[sighs]

610
00:38:13.060 --> 00:38:14.629
Nice and relaxed.

611
00:38:16.564 --> 00:38:17.598
[breathes deeply]

612
00:38:19.600 --> 00:38:20.635
Ah.

613
00:38:21.736 --> 00:38:23.271
It's like you're anticipating
the shot a little bit.

614
00:38:23.403 --> 00:38:25.006
I know. I know.

615
00:38:25.139 --> 00:38:27.842
I've took her to the range
a couple of times.
I squeeze. not pull.

616
00:38:30.745 --> 00:38:32.379
-It's okay.
-[sighs. laughs]

617
00:38:32.513 --> 00:38:35.116
All right. it'll come to you.
Takes some time.

618
00:38:35.249 --> 00:38:37.151
Look. I appreciate
the free lesson.

619
00:38:37.285 --> 00:38:39.887
I just think that
maybe this isn't for me.

620
00:38:40.021 --> 00:38:42.657
-The gun?
-Yes. the gun.

621
00:38:43.323 --> 00:38:44.491
Then why the hell
did you buy it?

622
00:38:44.625 --> 00:38:46.160
I don't know. I...

623
00:38:47.327 --> 00:38:49.130
thought I could use
a little bit more control.

624
00:38:49.263 --> 00:38:51.032
Not sure you're gonna
get that from a gun.

625
00:38:51.599 --> 00:38:54.268
You know. I moved 12 times
before I even went
to high school.

626
00:38:55.169 --> 00:38:56.604
Twelve times.

627
00:38:56.737 --> 00:38:58.906
New city. new school. new base.

628
00:38:59.040 --> 00:39:02.910
It was like everywhere I went.
I was a stranger.

629
00:39:03.044 --> 00:39:04.377
Yeah. I kinda know how that is.

630
00:39:04.512 --> 00:39:05.546
[Reenie sighs]

631
00:39:07.048 --> 00:39:10.718
It teaches you. though.
how to rely on yourself. right?

632
00:39:11.819 --> 00:39:13.521
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

633
00:39:13.654 --> 00:39:16.624
And I got that from you
the moment I met you.
I could tell.

634
00:39:16.757 --> 00:39:18.292
Well. it could have gone
a very different way.

635
00:39:18.425 --> 00:39:19.827
How's that?

636
00:39:20.460 --> 00:39:21.863
I was a mess.

637
00:39:21.996 --> 00:39:24.298
-[chuckles]
-I was an absolute nightmare
for my mom.

638
00:39:24.431 --> 00:39:27.301
and I was expelled from school
multiple times.

639
00:39:27.434 --> 00:39:29.904
It was like the greatest hits
of a troubled teen.

640
00:39:30.403 --> 00:39:32.707
And I ticked every single box.

641
00:39:33.674 --> 00:39:35.509
I was on the wrong side
of the courtroom.

642
00:39:36.043 --> 00:39:38.445
-You?
-Mm-hmm. Yeah.

643
00:39:40.147 --> 00:39:41.682
What made you change?

644
00:39:43.050 --> 00:39:45.253
[sighs] I don't know. I...

645
00:39:47.221 --> 00:39:49.489
I think I was acting out
'cause I was...

646
00:39:51.491 --> 00:39:52.727
feeling invisible.

647
00:39:53.661 --> 00:39:54.729
[Colter] Mmm.

648
00:39:55.997 --> 00:40:01.936
I just so badly wanted someone
to care enough to try
and come save me.

649
00:40:03.604 --> 00:40:07.241
But at some point. I realized
that I was gonna have to be
that person for myself.

650
00:40:08.843 --> 00:40:10.410
And from then on. I was.

651
00:40:13.214 --> 00:40:15.149
Then after
what happened last year...

652
00:40:16.284 --> 00:40:18.451
[sighs] I don't know.
It was like...

653
00:40:19.921 --> 00:40:21.622
I just reverted into some...

654
00:40:23.391 --> 00:40:27.295
scared little girl who had
no control over anything.

655
00:40:28.029 --> 00:40:33.834
and I guess I just lost myself.

656
00:40:36.370 --> 00:40:37.772
[breathes shakily]

657
00:40:37.905 --> 00:40:40.608
I think that's the first time
I've ever said that out loud.

658
00:40:45.478 --> 00:40:48.516
You got a lot of people
who care a lot about you.
you know that?

659
00:40:49.583 --> 00:40:52.253
You do. People who would
do anything for you.

660
00:40:53.521 --> 00:40:54.755
No matter what.

661
00:40:56.123 --> 00:40:57.158
And you're strong.

662
00:40:58.458 --> 00:41:00.294
That's why you're so good
at what you do.

663
00:41:02.096 --> 00:41:03.197
You don't break easy.

664
00:41:08.069 --> 00:41:09.103
Thank you.

665
00:41:13.507 --> 00:41:16.043
-[Reenie groans] Mm-hmm.
-About this target practice
here?

666
00:41:16.177 --> 00:41:18.446
-All right.
-[chuckles]

667
00:41:21.582 --> 00:41:23.084
-Ugh.
-It'll come to you. Come on.

668
00:41:23.217 --> 00:41:25.353
-Okay. Well.
maybe with some help.
-Yeah.

669
00:41:25.485 --> 00:41:27.355
[breathes deeply]

670
00:41:30.257 --> 00:41:33.661
Okay. so this-this. uh.
wrong side of the courtroom
thing. by the way.

671
00:41:33.794 --> 00:41:35.062
are we talking misdemeanor.
felony?

672
00:41:35.196 --> 00:41:37.865
-Oh. wow. Look at that.
-Who am I hanging out with?

673
00:41:37.999 --> 00:41:39.467
I bail you out of jail
a few times.

674
00:41:39.600 --> 00:41:41.302
you really learn
a thing or two. huh?

675
00:41:41.435 --> 00:41:42.436
[chuckles]

676
00:41:43.004 --> 00:41:44.572
Hey. there we go. See?

677
00:41:44.705 --> 00:41:46.640
-Better. Better.
-Right. Way... Way better.

678
00:41:47.375 --> 00:41:49.443
-[gunfire]
-[laughs]

679
00:41:50.144 --> 00:41:51.178
Worse.
